    <section class="banner-carousel-card grid_wrapper grid_wrapper--large">
      <div class="heading-container">
                <h3>
          Challenges affecting UK seas
        </h3>
              </div>
      <div class="splide">
        <div class="splide__track">
          <ul class="splide__list">
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/addressing-unsustainable-fishing-and-seafood" data-link-text="How we&#039;re tackling unsustainable fishing">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Tackling unsustainable fishing</h4>
                                            <p>Fishing isn’t a problem but overfishing is. We promote sustainable fishing practices and work with governments and the European Union to shape policy. The European review of the Common Fisheries Policy in 2013 included most of the changes and commitments we’d been asking for – like an aim to end overfishing and the wasteful practice of ‘discards’.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                          <div class="btn-wrap">
                        <div class="btn-wrap--item">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/addressing-unsustainable-fishing-and-seafood" class="btn btn--white">
                            How we&#039;re tackling unsustainable fishing
                          </a>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/climate-change-and-energy" data-link-text="Learn more about climate change">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Climate change</h4>
                                            <p>The UK seas have huge wind, wave and tidal power potential with Scotland in particular is doing its bit to move towards a low carbon, renewable energy future. But these green sources of energy need to be well planned and managed. We work with governments and the renewable energy industry to make sure the industry grows without harming the environment and wildlife.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                          <div class="btn-wrap">
                        <div class="btn-wrap--item">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/climate-change-and-energy" class="btn btn--white">
                            Learn more about climate change
                          </a>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="" data-link-text="Find out more">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Improving management of UK seas</h4>
                                            <p>With so many industries operating in the UK’s seas it is vital that they manage their activity in a sustainable way that doesn’t harm the environment and wildlife. We bring together governments, industry, scientists and conservationists to make sure that they work together to manage the seas and look at their combined effect on the environment.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                      </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-pagination-container">
          <div class="splide-arrows-bg">
            <div class="splide__arrows splide__arrows--ltr">
              <button
                class="splide__arrow splide__arrow--prev"
                type="button"
                aria-label="Previous slide"
                aria-controls="splide01-track"
              >
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 40 40" width="40" height="40" focusable="false">
                  <path d="m15.5 0.932-4.3 4.38 14.5 14.6-14.5 14.5 4.3 4.4 14.6-14.6 4.4-4.3-4.4-4.4-14.6-14.6z"></path>
                </svg>
              </button>
              <div class="banner-carousel-pagination">
                <p><span class="banner-carousel-current"></span>/<span class="banner-carousel-total"></span></p>
              </div>
              <button
                class="splide__arrow splide__arrow--next"
                type="button"
                aria-label="Next slide"
                aria-controls="splide01-track"
              >
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 40 40" width="40" height="40" focusable="false">
                  <path d="m15.5 0.932-4.3 4.38 14.5 14.6-14.5 14.5 4.3 4.4 14.6-14.6 4.4-4.3-4.4-4.4-14.6-14.6z"></path>
                </svg>
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="desktop-cta-button-container">
            <div class="btn-wrap">
              <div class="btn-wrap--item">
                <a href="" class="btn btn--white">
                  Find out more
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
       </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</section>

<section id="why-uk-seas-and-coasts-are-important" class="banner banner--success banner--callout_right paragraph-container">
    <picture class="banner_image">
        <source srcset="/sites/default/files/2018-01/Medium_WW236066.jpg" media="(max-width: 750px)">
        <source srcset="/sites/default/files/2018-01/Medium_WW236066.jpg" media="(max-width: 1024px)">
        <img srcset="/sites/default/files/2018-01/Medium_WW236066.jpg" >
    </picture>
    <div class="content">
        <div class="callout_box">
          <div class="callout_scroll">
            <span class="tag">Success Story</span>
            <h2 class="title">
              Legal protection for our seas
            </h2>
            <p>We&#039;ve campaigned for years to persuade UK governments to pass legal ‘Marine Acts’ to protect our seas – and by 2010 we’d succeeded in getting a UK and Scottish Marine Act. 
The Acts provide plans for better management of UK seas – including a commitment to introduce specific marine protected areas. We now need to hold our governments to their word and make sure a big enough network of properly-managed protected areas are created. 
We also led the PISCES project and the Celtic Seas Partnership to bring together politicians, scientists and industries to set up collaborative and innovative approaches to managing the UK and Celtic Seas. We believe that putting the people that use the sea at the heart of management and giving them the opportunity to influence how their seas are managed is vital in keeping the UK’s seas healthy.
</p>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

